									"patching_rect" : [ 503.0, 192.0, 663.0, 51.0 ],
									"text" : "Explanation: we need a parameter index added on to the module name, as this is used as an address in the coll. If we just used the module name on its own as the address, followed by a list of parameters, then each set of parameters would overwrite the previous one (because it would have the same address in the coll). + is used to join the module name and the parameter index, as this makes it easier to seperate the name and the index when the data is later retrieved"
